---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - useUtils" 
  description="Learn about our 100% client-side privacy guarantee. We do not transmit, collect, or store any of your private keys or tokens."
  keywords="privacy policy, useutils privacy, local-first privacy, client-side tools security"
>
  <Header />

  <!-- Main Body Content -->
  <main class="flex-grow w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-2 pb-6 border-b border-border-hairline/60">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 font-sans">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
        Last updated: June 10, 2026. Your privacy is protected by design: all computations occur entirely inside your browser.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline rounded-xl p-6 md:p-10 shadow-sm flex flex-col gap-8">
      
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          1. The Local-First Privacy Guarantee
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          Unlike traditional web utilities that process data on backend servers, <strong class="text-zinc-200">useUtils</strong> functions entirely inside your client browser sandbox. When you encode, decode, sign tokens, build configuration files, query local SQLite databases (via WebAssembly), or parse raw payloads, the computations are handled 100% locally by client-side APIs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          2. Ephemeral P2P WebRTC Signaling
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          Our experimental WebRTC sharing tools (such as P2P File Sharing) establish direct point-to-point data streams. To establish the connection, we utilize a temporary, stateless signaling server solely to broker network metadata (SDP offers/answers and ICE candidate maps). The signaling server is completely serverless (hosted on Cloudflare Workers), holds zero logs, records zero file details, and terminates immediately once the peer handshake completes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          3. Browser Sandbox Storage
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          To improve user experience, some tools may store non-sensitive preference indexes or project configuration templates locally inside your browser's <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-800 text-zinc-300 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5">localStorage</code> or <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-800 text-zinc-300 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5">IndexedDB</code>. We never store sensitive credentials, parsed files, database tables, or cryptographic secrets on our servers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          4. Updates to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans pl-4">
          As our multi-workspace platform grows (including new Playgrounds, Config tools, and Cheatsheets), we will continue to adhere to our strict client-side-only execution standard. Any updates to this policy will reflect this core architectural constraint.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer Info Box -->
      <div class="mt-4 p-5 bg-zinc-900/30 border border-border-hairline rounded-lg flex items-start gap-3.5">
        <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-accent-emerald shrink-0 mt-1"></div>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-zinc-200">Privacy Audit Tool:</strong> You can inspect our open-source codebase directly or view the network tab in your browser's Developer Tools to confirm that no server data transmissions occur.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
